function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    if !isa(dt,DateTime)
        throw(ArgumentError("Only DateTime objects are supported."))
    end
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end
```
This function takes a `DateTime` object and an optional integer argument `bump`, which defaults to 3 hours. It then checks whether the input is a valid `DateTime` object, and throws an error if it's not. Finally, it adds the desired number of hours (defaulting to +3) to the input `DateTime` object using the `Dates.Hour` function from the `Dates` module, and returns the resulting `DateTime` object.

Note that this function only works with `DateTime` objects, and throws an error if a `Date` object is provided as input.
